@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy";
}

<div class="page-header mb-4">
    <span class="eyebrow">Policy</span>
    <h1 class="display-6 fw-semibold">Privacy and data handling</h1>
    <p class="text-secondary mb-0">This application stores community data in SQLite and provides modules for posts, services, and marketplace listings.</p>
</div>

<div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-4">
    <div class="card-body p-4">
        <h2 class="h5 mb-3">Privacy overview</h2>
        <p class="mb-0">
            CommunitySystem is intended for internal community use. Content you create (for example, posts, comments, Lost &amp; Found reports, complaint submissions, marketplace listings, and chat messages) is stored within this application to support the service features.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-4">
    <div class="card-body p-4">
        <h2 class="h5 mb-3">Marketplace disclaimer (financial &amp; transactions)</h2>
        <div class="alert alert-warning mb-3">
            <strong>Important:</strong> Marketplace payments are arranged directly between users. The management team and this platform do not verify sellers, buyers, items, pricing, payment proofs, or delivery/collection outcomes.
        </div>
        <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>All purchases, rentals, and payments are made <strong>at your own risk</strong>.</li>
            <li>Users are responsible for verifying item condition, authenticity, ownership, and legality before transacting.</li>
            <li>Uploaded payment QR codes are provided by users; always confirm the payee and amount in your e-wallet app before paying.</li>
            <li>Resolve disputes directly with the other party. Report suspicious or illegal listings to administrators for review/removal.</li>
            <li>Do not share sensitive information in chat (bank passwords, OTP codes, full card numbers).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
    <div class="card-body p-4">
        <h2 class="h5 mb-3">Data &amp; security notes</h2>
        <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>Keep your account credentials private and log out on shared devices.</li>
            <li>Uploaded files (images/attachments) may be visible to other authenticated users depending on the module.</li>
            <li>Before production use, define retention rules, administrator access procedures, and incident response processes.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
